2
00:00:09.696 --> 00:00:13.151
As we said, music is the rational
organization of sounds and

3
00:00:13.151 --> 00:00:15.510
silences passing through time.

4
00:00:15.510 --> 00:00:18.370
That's my definition,
you can have your own, and

5
00:00:18.370 --> 00:00:21.510
it's a general one, maybe a bit wordy.

6
00:00:21.510 --> 00:00:24.220
A more down to Earth definition
would say that music,

7
00:00:24.220 --> 00:00:29.890
indeed any sound,
is simply a disturbance of the atmosphere.

8
00:00:29.890 --> 00:00:33.990
But music is a regularly organized
disturbance of the atmosphere resulting in

9
00:00:33.990 --> 00:00:37.290
sound waves coming in regular patterns.

10
00:00:37.290 --> 00:00:41.810
Sound waves are simply
differing air pressures.

11
00:00:41.810 --> 00:00:45.710
Air being compressed,
or air being expanded.

12
00:00:45.710 --> 00:00:48.720
And the pattern is regularly repeated.

13
00:00:48.720 --> 00:00:53.370
We have large sound waves,
and smaller sound waves.

14
00:00:53.370 --> 00:00:56.570
Large ones generate low pitches.

15
00:00:56.570 --> 00:00:58.780
Small ones generate high pitches.

16
00:00:59.970 --> 00:01:06.425
A very long string creates an equally
long sound and a low sound.

17
00:01:06.425 --> 00:01:10.376
[SOUND].

18
00:01:10.376 --> 00:01:16.350
Now, this string on the piano here,
is vibrating at about 30 times per second.

19
00:01:16.350 --> 00:01:19.446
The highest note on the piano,
[SOUND] way up here,

20
00:01:19.446 --> 00:01:24.338
the highest note on the piano is
vibrating about 4,000 times per second.

21
00:01:24.338 --> 00:01:29.660
We don't hear all those 4,000 vibrations,
but they can be measured in a laboratory.

22
00:01:31.540 --> 00:01:34.260
Let's take a look at a diagram.

23
00:01:34.260 --> 00:01:39.280
It shows a pitch on top and
multiples of it underneath.

24
00:01:39.280 --> 00:01:44.070
Did you see four pitches here on this
particular screen from top to bottom?

25
00:01:44.070 --> 00:01:49.870
The top one is shaking, vibrating,
about 110 times per second.

26
00:01:50.990 --> 00:01:55.585
If we double the vibration to 220
times per second we get this sound.

27
