00:02:30.121 --> 00:02:32.546
heard through the atmosphere.

35
00:02:32.546 --> 00:02:36.140
220, well that's a little
less than 6 feet.

36
00:02:36.140 --> 00:02:38.650
A 440 somewhat less than 3 feet.

37
00:02:38.650 --> 00:02:42.790
Obviously to be heard,
sound must reach the ear.

38
00:02:44.090 --> 00:02:47.730
Once there,
sound waves enter the inner ear.

39
00:02:47.730 --> 00:02:52.010
And ultimately are changed into
electro chemical impulses.

40
00:02:52.010 --> 00:02:57.680
The heavy lifting here occurs in a small
organ called the basilar membrane.

41
00:02:59.270 --> 00:03:05.125
Here, filaments, called cilia
are activated by particular sound waves.

42
00:03:05.125 --> 00:03:09.870
In other words,
the basilar membrane is tonotopic.

43
00:03:09.870 --> 00:03:14.180
Each of the many cilia responds to
only one frequency, high or low.

44
00:03:15.260 --> 00:03:20.650
When stimulated by a particular
sound wave, the cilia send a signal.

45
00:03:20.650 --> 00:03:25.630
Hey brain, heads up,
the frequency A-440 is coming in.

46
00:03:25.630 --> 00:03:31.280
The sound goes to the brain,
through first the primary

47
00:03:31.280 --> 00:03:35.790
auditory nerve, and then, to the left and
right side of the cortex.

48
00:03:35.790 --> 00:03:41.230
So here on the screen, you see the left
side of the brain, the left cortex.

49
00:03:41.230 --> 00:03:46.020
In the gray area, we have the temporal
lobe, and within the temporal lobe,

50
00:03:46.020 --> 00:03:52.900
the primary auditory cortex where much
of the processing of sound occurs.

51
00:03:52.900 --> 00:03:54.646
It too is tonotopic.

52
00:03:54.646 --> 00:03:59.680
The neurons there respond only
to particular frequencies.

53
00:03:59.680 --> 00:04:03.540
All of this is something of a
simplification, but it gives you a general

54
00:04:03.540 --> 00:04:09.190
sense of what is happening as musical
sounds enter our ear and our brain.

55
00:04:10.580 --> 00:04:12.360
And it's complex,

56
00:04:12.360 --> 00:04:15.710
because many parts of the brain
are engaged when we listen to music.

57
00:04:15.710 --> 00:04:20.770
The frontal lobe, as you see out there
to the left in the green color, and

58
00:04:20.770 --> 00:04:22.550
the prefrontal lobe.

59
